org.gbif.api.vocabulary

Enum ThreatStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ThreatStatus>
      • org.gbif.api.vocabulary.ThreatStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ThreatStatus>

    public enum ThreatStatus
extends Enum<ThreatStatus>
    The IUCN threat status. The IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria are intended to be an easily and widely understood system for classifying species at high risk of global extinction. The general aim of the system is to provide an explicit, objective framework for the classification of the broadest range of species according to their extinction risk.
    See Also:
    rs.gbif.org vocabulary
